The paper proposes a mathematical model for a two-sided data market and constructs algorithms for such a market to function. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the monetization of data and pre-trained models, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges associated with data as an asset, which could be related to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a truthful, zero regret mechanism to auction a class of combinatorial goods, which could be related to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
